        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 11:50PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 1150 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 18
miles north of Shepherd, or 19 miles southeast of Roundup, moving
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of Southeastern Musselshell and Northeastern
Yellowstone Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
